<p>
phpMyAdmin security announcement
</p>
<hr>
<p>
Announcement-ID: PMASA-2008-9<br />
Date: 2008-10-30<br />
</p>
<p>
<b>Summary</b>:<br />
XSS on a Designer component 
</p>
<p>
<b>Description</b>:<br />
A logged-in user can be subject of cross site scripting attack via the <tt>pmd_pdf.php</tt> script.
</p>
<p>
<b>Severity</b>:<br />
We consider this vulnerability to be serious.
</p>
<p>
<b>Affected versions</b>:<br />
For 2.11.x: versions before 2.11.9.3.<br />
For 3.0.x: versions before 3.0.1.1.<br />
</p>
<p>
<b>Solution:</b><br />
Upgrade to phpMyAdmin 2.11.9.3 or 3.0.1.1.
</p>
<b>References:</b><br />
<a href="http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/31928/info">Advisory: http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/31928/info</a><br />
<p>
In case of questions, please contact the
phpMyAdmin team. Our website is <a href="http://www.phpmyadmin.net">http://www.phpmyadmin.net/</a>.
</p>

